The House included immigration provisions in a bill for U.S. operations in Iraq and Afghanistan.
The REAL ID Act aims to prevent illegal immigrants from obtaining driver's licenses to enhance security.
Critics argue it will harm immigrant communities and create unintended consequences.
The Act, championed by Sensenbrenner, is seen as a counterterrorism measure.
However, opponents believe it is anti-immigrant and lacks proper vetting.
Some fear it could lead to a national ID card and hinder asylum seekers.
Lawmakers are divided on the issue, with some pushing for stronger immigration controls.
The debate continues on the potential impact of the REAL ID Act.
